### BACKGROUND IMAGE ###
if you use directly an image, it could corupt your grub menu (it'll reboot instead of showing your menu).

source of the image: Gloria.jpg from the Linux Mint package "mint-backgrounds-retro_1.3_all.deb".

DO USE THE CONVERT FUNCTION TO BE SURE THAT YOUR GRUB WILL STILL BOOT

for example:
sudo convert /usr/share/backgrounds/linuxmint-retro/Gloria.jpg -resize 1920x1080! -sharpen 5.0x1.3 -quality 80 -brightness-contrast -52x-48 -gamma 1.2 /boot/grub/themes/Crunchy-distro-ish/mint/Gloria.jpg

The sudo is only to have the right to write a file in the /boot folder. The other settings are to dark the image.

### FONTS ###
the font, in grub, can be loaded only in one size per file. You can make the pf2 file with that command:

sudo grub-mkfont -s 18 -o /boot/grub/themes/Crunchy-distro-ish/OpenSans_normal.pf2 /usr/share/fonts/truetype/Open_Sans/OpenSans-Light.ttf -v
or
sudo grub-mkfont -s 32 -o /boot/grub/themes/Crunchy-distro-ish/OpenSans_title.pf2 /usr/share/fonts/truetype/Open_Sans/OpenSans-Light.ttf -v

-s: size
-o: output
-v: verbose (necessary to know how to call the font in theme.txt)

you can add too
-b: bold

The errors messages doesn't bother the efficiency of the resulted pf2 files.
The font can be found here: https://fonts.google.com/specimen/Open+Sans

Source for more than 800 fonts : https://fonts.google.com/
